						               													<description>These rules adapt Warlord Games&amp;rsquo; Strontium Dog skirmish game for solo play. &amp;#10;You take the role of a mutant Search/Destroy agent, tracking down wanted criminals across the universe.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Bounty Hunter is a mini&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#144;campaign using the Strontium Dog solo play rules, allowing you to play a series of interlocking games.&amp;#10;Of course, if you prefer you can easily adapt this mini&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#144;campaign to the regular rules for Strontium Dog, playing against your friends face&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#144;to&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#144;face.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You&amp;rsquo;ll need the following to play Bounty Hunter:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Various Strontium Dog models. You can easily adapt the game to suit your own model collection.&amp;#10;     Terrain representing the battleground, and a surface to play on &amp;ndash; a 3&amp;rsquo; x 3&amp;rsquo; tabletop should suffice, although the scenarios are best played on a 4&amp;rsquo; x 4&amp;rsquo; area.&amp;#10;     The Strontium Dog rules, and necessary gaming paraphernalia (dice, etc.)&amp;#10;     The various cards (Confrontation cards, Foe cards and Friend cards) needed for the solo play version of Strontium Dog &amp;ndash; you can find these on pages 20&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#144;34 of the rules (print them out, cut them out and reinforce them by glueing them to card).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Before you begin the game, you&amp;rsquo;ll first have to create a Strontium Dog who will represent you, scouring the galaxy for criminals. This process is described in full in the campaign rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ndash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
